#
# <jcl-install-dir>/test
# Root of all JCL JUnit tests.  To run tests do:
# 1) Download and install the JUnit 3.7 or later from http://www.junit.org
# 2) Set your JCL_HOME and build JCL (see <jcl-install-dir>/build.xml for details
# 3) Run using Ant from <jcl-install-dir> with:
#    %ant test
# 4) Alternatively if you have the <jcl-install-dir>/bin set in your CLASSPATH then
#    you can run the JUnit tests by doing:
#    %java junit.textui.TestRunner jpos.AllTests 
# @author E. Michael Maximilien (maxim@us.ibm.com)
# @since 2.1.0
#
